My daughter ordered a berry crepe with chocolate sauce (no Nutella due to her nut allergy) and a strawberry frappe. She absolutely loved both as well!

Salomay Coffee Shop is truly a hidden gem! From the moment you walk in, you‚Äôre greeted with a warm and inviting atmosphere that makes you feel right at home. The cozy vibe, excellent service, and top-notch coffee make it a place you‚Äôll want to visit again and again.Highly recommend to anyone who loves great coffee, crepes, and great people!

detailedReviews.author: Remi K
detailedReviews.text: This place is a great example as to why you wait and visit a few times before finally giving a review. The first couple of times i first tried this place, amazing. The wait for basic french toast was a bit much but hey, the presentation was nice and the frappes were made perfectly....until they weren't. I guess my first few visits I was lucky but afterwards, the place's service went down hill extremely fast. 20 minutes. No one should have to sit in a drive thru lane for 20 minutes just for you to drizzle syrup on 2 slices of thin bread. And this isn't a one time thing. I constantly wait at least 10-15 minutes in the drive thru lane and there is NO ONE else around. I can make french toast in under 10 minutes tops. The frappes are no longer good. Extremely watery and no longer created the way they were the first few times I had them. This one visit, I asked if they could make it thick since it is basically water by the time i get home. The girl added a giant wad of ice to it which lost any flavor i had paid to taste. so now i just have thick icy flavored water and basic french toast that took almost half an hour to make. You can take a mini nap in the drive thru and wake up and still not have your order ready. I was able to accomplish that today. Food and drink were both tossed out and I'm heading to CFA where consistency never fails. This is the last time i give my money to this place. Consistency is key, please work on it for your other customers.

detailedReviews.author: Matthew P
detailedReviews.text:
Salomay in McKinney is a delightful culinary gem, and their berry crepe is nothing short of a masterpiece. From the moment it arrives at your table, the vibrant colors of the fresh berries catch your eye. Each bite is a perfect balance of sweetness and tartness, complemented by the light, fluffy crepe that melts in your mouth.

Pairing perfectly with the crepe is their delicious iced coffee, which is smooth and refreshing, providing just the right kick to balance the sweetness of the dish. The rich flavor of the coffee enhances the overall experience, making it an ideal match.

The presentation of the crepe is as impressive as the flavor, showcasing a beautiful arrangement of seasonal berries, topped with a dusting of powdered sugar. The chef‚Äôs attention to detail truly shines through. Whether you‚Äôre enjoying it for breakfast or dessert, this combination is a must-try.

The warm, welcoming atmosphere of Salomay makes the experience even more enjoyable. I can‚Äôt recommend their berry crepe and iced coffee highly enough‚Äîboth are delicious treats that will leave you craving more!

negative.author: Geralynne Solitaire
negative.text: This placed popped up on my IG with a Biscoff Latte and was so excited to try as I try new places a lot. Most mid latte ever. It took a while to get even though it was not busy and the ice was completely melted so it was extremely watered down. The only flavor of biscoff was the biscoff on the side of the cup. Will not be back.

negative.author: Remi K
negative.text: This place is a great example as to why you wait and visit a few times before finally giving a review. The first couple of times i first tried this place, amazing. The wait for basic french toast was a bit much but hey, the presentation was nice and the frappes were made perfectly....until they weren't. I guess my first few visits I was lucky but afterwards, the place's service went down hill extremely fast. 20 minutes. No one should have to sit in a drive thru lane for 20 minutes just for you to drizzle syrup on 2 slices of thin bread. And this isn't a one time thing. I constantly wait at least 10-15 minutes in the drive thru lane and there is NO ONE else around. I can make french toast in under 10 minutes tops. The frappes are no longer good. Extremely watery and no longer created the way they were the first few times I had them. This one visit, I asked if they could make it thick since it is basically water by the time i get home. The girl added a giant wad of ice to it which lost any flavor i had paid to taste. so now i just have thick icy flavored water and basic french toast that took almost half an hour to make. You can take a mini nap in the drive thru and wake up and still not have your order ready. I was able to accomplish that today. Food and drink were both tossed out and I'm heading to CFA where consistency never fails. This is the last time i give my money to this place. Consistency is key, please work on it for your other customers.
